		<part id="why">
			<title>Why Microservices?</title>
			<slide id="speed-and-safety">
				<title>Speed and Safety for API Products</title>
				<ul>
					<li>API products should be easy to add, change, and remove</li>
					<ul>
						<li>This may apply only to the public and partner APIs</li>
						<li>Mature API strategies look at <em>every capability</em> as an API product</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Traditional enterprise IT can take a long time to approve anything</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Only a fraction of these blockers are rooted in business needs</li>
					</ul>
					<li>The Web allows <em>permissionless decentralized innovation</em> at global scale</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Minimal technical requirements (Internet connectivity and URI/HTTP/HTML)</li>
						<li>Services start, evolve, and die in a feedback loop for individual services</li>
						<li>Harder to grasp and manage than one centralized implementation platform</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
